author: akarasulu
msg: The getSuffix() method has been altered to return Names instead of Strings
for the Dn return type.  Also note that an extra boolean method argument
was added to getSuffix() to control whether or not a normalized Dn or the
original user provided Dn is to be returned by the method.
All methods returning a Name must provide the option of returning either
the normalized form or the user provided form.  The caller should know in
advance which form is required and situations exist where one is preferred
over the other.

author: akarasulu
msg: Changes in the AtomicBackend for getSuffix() have resulted in changes to
listSuffixes() which now will return a Iterator over Names as opposed to
Strings for AtomicBackend suffixes.
The getSuffix() and getMatchedDn() methods have been altered to return
Names instead of Strings for the Dn returns.  Also note that an extra
boolean method argument was added to listSuffixes(), getMatchedDn(), and
getSuffix() to control whether or not a normalized Dn or the original
user provided Dn is to be returned by the method.
All methods returning a Name must provide the option of returning either
the normalized form or the user provided form.  The caller should know in
advance which form is required and situations exist where one is preferred
over the other.
